{
  "texts": [
    "While we eventualy refilled, the model did train for some number of steps wherein serper would continuously return errors, as seen by the drop in reward and sequence length.",
    "However, despite this, our overall model performance continued to improve, with step 1900 being significantly better than step 1000 (right before the serper credit issue).",
    "This suggests our training is somewhat robust to server-side tool errors, and exploring the degree of this robustness is an interesting avenue for future investigation.",
    "In this section, we detail how we estimate the cost of deep research models.",
    "For proprietary models, we use the actual billed costs reported in their API consoles."
  ]
}